## Implementation Steps

- [ ] **Story 5.1: Implement Backend Logic and API for Application Backup**
  - [ ] Create API endpoint for backup initiation (`POST /api/admin/system/backup`)
  - [ ] Implement backup process as background task (separate from HTTP request-response cycle)
  - [ ] Define data to be included in backup (SQLite DB, avatars, URL favicons, branding)
  - [ ] Create backup manifest file with `backupCreatedAtTimestamp`, `databaseSchemaVersionId`, and optional `applicationVersion`
  - [ ] Implement backup archive creation and storage as `.zip` file with timestamped name
  - [ ] Add API response and feedback mechanisms (HTTP 202 Accepted for async initiation)
  - [ ] Ensure database integrity during backup (using SQLite online backup API)
  - [ ] Exclude environment files (`.env`, `.env.local`) from backup
  - Success criteria: Asynchronous backup process with manifest creation
  - Dependencies: Epic 1, Epic 2 (Admin Routes)

- [ ] **Story 5.1.5: Implement API Endpoints for Managing Backup Files**
  - [ ] Create API endpoint for listing backup files (`GET /api/admin/system/backups`)
  - [ ] Implement backup file download endpoint (`GET /api/admin/system/backups/[filename]`)
  - [ ] Add backup file deletion endpoint (`DELETE /api/admin/system/backups/[filename]`)
  - [ ] Ensure proper security for all endpoints (admin-only access, filename validation)
  - [ ] Implement sorted listing (newest first) with file metadata
  - Success criteria: Complete API for backup file management
  - Dependencies: Story 5.1

- [ ] **Story 5.2: Implement Backend Logic and API for Application Restore**
  - [ ] Create API endpoint for restore initiation (`POST /api/admin/system/restore`)
  - [ ] Implement backup validation in background task (verify structure, required files)
  - [ ] Add manifest reading functionality (log timestamp, schema version, app version)
  - [ ] Create database restoration and migration process (temp backup, replace, run migrations)
  - [ ] Implement asset file restoration (only if DB restore successful)
  - [ ] Add API response and feedback mechanisms (HTTP 202 Accepted for async initiation)
  - [ ] Implement proper error handling (rollback to temp DB backup if migration fails)
  - Success criteria: Reliable restore process with proper order and error handling
  - Dependencies: Story 5.1

- [ ] **Story 5.3: Develop Admin UI for Backup, Restore, and Backup File Management**
  - [ ] Create system operations admin page (`/admin/system/operations`)
  - [ ] Implement backup file listing and management UI (MUI Table/List with actions)
  - [ ] Add UI for initiating new backups (async with proper feedback)
  - [ ] Create restore from backup UI with warnings and fresh backup suggestion
  - [ ] Implement asynchronous feedback for operations (Snackbars, loading states)
  - [ ] Add UI lockdown during restore initiation with refresh button
  - Success criteria: Intuitive UI for backup and restore operations
  - Dependencies: Stories 5.1, 5.1.5, 5.2

- [ ] **Story 5.4: Implement Basic System Statistics Display**
  - [ ] Create statistics section in admin dashboard (`/admin` or `/admin/stats`)
  - [ ] Implement backend API for statistics (`GET /api/admin/statistics/summary`)
  - [ ] Add UI for displaying user, group, and URL counts (MUI Cards/List)
  - [ ] Implement loading states (MUI Skeleton) and error handling
  - [ ] Add optional refresh button for statistics
  - Success criteria: Admin dashboard displays key system statistics
  - Dependencies: Epic 2 (Admin Dashboard)

- [ ] **Story 5.5: Implement Basic User Activity Tracking Log**
  - [ ] Create ActivityLog Prisma model with comprehensive fields (timestamp, user details, action type, details as JSON)
  - [ ] Implement backend logging service with `createActivityLogEntry` function
  - [ ] Add logging for key system actions (login, user management, branding, URL/Group management, system ops)
  - [ ] Create admin UI for viewing activity log (`/admin/activity-log`)
  - [ ] Implement backend API for log retrieval with pagination
  - [ ] Ensure no sensitive data is logged
  - Success criteria: Comprehensive activity tracking with admin UI
  - Dependencies: Epic 1 (User Schema)

- [ ] **Story 5.6: Implement Configurable Log Retention Policy**
  - [ ] Update SystemSetting schema with logRetentionDays (default 180, 0=keep indefinitely)
  - [ ] Create admin UI for log retention configuration
  - [ ] Implement backend API for policy management
  - [ ] Add automated log pruning scheduled task via node-cron (daily 3 AM)
  - [ ] Create manual log pruning trigger with confirmation dialog
  - [ ] Implement logging of pruning operations to ActivityLog
  - Success criteria: Configurable log retention with automated and manual pruning
  - Dependencies: Story 5.5

## Affected Components

- Database schema (ActivityLog, SystemSetting)
- Admin API endpoints for system operations
- Admin UI for backup, restore, and monitoring
- Background processing for async operations
- Scheduled tasks for maintenance
- File system storage for backups (`/data/backups/`)

## Dependencies

- Epic 1 (Authentication, User Schema)
- Epic 2 (Admin Dashboard)
- node-cron for scheduled tasks (daily pruning at 3 AM)
- formidable for file uploads
- archiver for creating zip archives
- unzipper for extracting zip archives
- Prisma ORM for database operations

## Technical Considerations

- Backup and restore operations must be asynchronous (separate from HTTP request-response cycle)
- Database migrations must be handled properly during restore (equivalent to `npx prisma migrate deploy`)
- Log pruning must not impact system performance (scheduled for low-traffic time)
- Manifest format must be consistent and validated (JSON with required fields)
- Security for backup/restore operations is critical (admin-only access, file validation)
- Backup storage location must be secure and not publicly accessible
- Environmental variables must be excluded from backups
- Activity log must not contain sensitive data
- All operations must provide appropriate user feedback

## Documentation Needs

- Full API documentation for all endpoints
- Detailed architecture document for async operations
- Component documentation for UI elements
- Testing documentation for backup/restore operations
- Admin guide for system operations
- Security considerations document

